channel.description:
[center][b]Creating Your First C# Application by Bebemycat2[/b][/center]

What you'll need

[ul][li]Visual c# express edition (http://msdn.microsoft.com/vstudio/express/downloads/)[/li]
[li]Common sense[/li][/ul]


Ok so lets begin:

Open up the C# IDE.
On the '[b]File[/b]' menu click '[b]New Project[/b]'. Make sure the '[b]Windows Application[/b]' template is selected then in the Name field, type 'HelloWorld', and click OK.

You should see a blank form like so:
[img]http://img207.imageshack.us/img207/9584/untitled2da0.jpg[/img]

Now on the [b]View[/b] menu, click [b]Toolbox[/b] to make the list of controls visible.
expand the [b]Common Controls[/b] list, and drag the [b]Label[/b] control to your form.

[img]http://img204.imageshack.us/img204/3479/untitlednz9.jpg[/img]

Also from the Toolbox Common Controls list, drag a [b]button[/b] onto the form, near the label.

Your form should now look like this:
[img]http://img207.imageshack.us/img207/3518/untitled3ky9.jpg[/img]

Double-click the new button to open the Code Editor. Visual C# has inserted a method called button1_Click that is executed when the button is clicked.

Your code so far should look like this:
[code=csharp]using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.ComponentModel;
using System.Data;
using System.Drawing;
using System.Text;
using System.Windows.Forms;

namespace WindowsApplication1
{
    public partial class Form1 : Form
    {
        public Form1()
        {
            InitializeComponent();
        }

        private void button1_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)
        {

        }
    }
}[/code]

Change your method 'private void button1_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)' to look like this:
[code=csharp]private void button1_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    label1.Text = "Hello, World!";
}[/code]

So your overall code should look like this:
[code=csharp]using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.ComponentModel;
using System.Data;
using System.Drawing;
using System.Text;
using System.Windows.Forms;

namespace WindowsApplication1
{
    public partial class Form1 : Form
    {
        public Form1()
        {
            InitializeComponent();
        }

        private void button1_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)
        {
            label1.Text = "Hello, World!";
        }
    }
}[/code]

Now press F5 to compile and run.


Some credit to http://msdn2.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms173060(VS.80).aspx where I learned my first C# application.
